

1. New c++ Project

2. Executable Hello World C++ Project(Toolchains : Linux GCC)

3. Project -> Properties -> C/C++ General -> Paths and Symbols
 -> <includes> tab -> GNU C++ -> ADD Header file

4. Project -> Properties -> C/C++ Build -> Settings
 -> <Tool Settings> tab -> GCC C++ Linker -> Libraries 
 -> Libraries(-l) add library file Name (ex/ libPocoCrypto.so => PocoCrypto)
 -> Library search path(-L) add library path (ex/ /usr/local/lib/)

5. Run Configurations -> C/C++ Application -> <Project Name> -> <Environment> tab
 -> New -> [Name : LD_LIBRARY_PATH] and [Value : <library path> (ex/ /usr/local/lib/)]

6. Run

-note-
PocoCrypto;PocoCryptod;PocoData;PocoDataSQLite;PocoDataSQLited;PocoDatad;PocoFoundation;PocoFoundationd;PocoJSON;PocoJSONd;PocoNet;PocoNetSSL;PocoNetSSLd;PocoNetd;PocoUtil;PocoUtild;PocoXML;PocoXMLd;
